class Solution:
    def generateTheString(self, n: int) -> str:
        # If n is odd, we can return a string with all the same character repeated n times
        if n % 2 == 1:
            return 'a' * n
        # If n is even, we can return a string with 'a' repeated (n-1) times and 'b' once
        else:
            return 'a' * (n - 1) + 'b'
```

This solution ensures that the generated string meets the requirement of having each character occur an odd number of times. If `n` is odd, the entire string can be composed of the same character, which will occur `n` times (an odd number). If `n` is even, the string can consist of `n-1` occurrences of one character and 1 occurrence of another, both of which are odd numbers.
